  "prompt": "How do I submit feedback to Quora?",
  "response": "To submit feedback to Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log In to Your Account:** Make sure you're logged into your Quora account.\n\n2. **Go to the Help Center:** Scroll to the bottom of the Quora homepage and click on \"Help\" or visit the Quora Help Center directly.\n\n3. **Submit a Request:** In the Help Center, there may be options for submitting feedback or reporting issues. Look for a \"Contact Us\" or \"Submit a Request\" link.\n\n4. **Provide Your Feedback:** Fill out any necessary fields, and provide your feedback in the description box. Be clear and concise about your thoughts or issues.\n\n5. **Submit Your Feedback:** Once you've completed the form, submit it. You should receive a confirmation that your feedback was sent.\n\nAlternatively, if you encounter specific issues or have feedback while using the site, you may also find a feedback link directly on the page you are visiting to submit your thoughts right at that moment.\n\nKeep in mind that there might not be a direct response to your feedback, but Quora does review user input for improvements.",
